WEBVTT

00:00:00.055 --> 00:00:25.865
Subtitle Provide by dramacool.asia Translator [Admin.@YNG]

00:00:30.655 --> 00:00:31.865
Hello, Ms. Choi.

00:00:31.948 --> 00:00:34.492
Ms. Ryu, I'm just leaving now.

00:00:34.576 --> 00:00:36.995
Do you know Ms. Cheon Sang-yeon,
by any chance?

00:00:40.957 --> 00:00:44.127
-Cheon Sang-yeon of Swallow Pictures?
-Yes.

00:00:48.256 --> 00:00:51.342
Yeah, I know her.
Who doesn't know Cheon Sang-yeon?

00:00:51.843 --> 00:00:54.763
I mean, do you know her personally?

00:00:56.681 --> 00:00:57.932
Personally?

00:00:59.934 --> 00:01:01.186
A little. Ages ago.

00:01:01.811 --> 00:01:04.230
It didn't seem like "a little, ages ago."

00:01:04.731 --> 00:01:07.692
You didn't watch the Baeksang Arts Awards
last night, did you?

00:01:08.234 --> 00:01:09.819
-No, I didn't.
-You should.

00:01:10.403 --> 00:01:13.490
Watch Ms. Cheon's acceptance speech
for Special Achievements in Film.

00:01:14.199 --> 00:01:15.492
Why? What did she say?

00:01:15.992 --> 00:01:18.953
Hello. I'm Cheon Sang-yeon,
the CEO of Swallow Pictures.

00:01:22.207 --> 00:01:23.041
Thank you.

00:01:25.502 --> 00:01:31.633
All movies are the fruits of
the talent and passion of their creators.

00:01:32.759 --> 00:01:34.427
If I, as a producer,

00:01:35.136 --> 00:01:37.347
can claim any credit in the process,

00:01:38.681 --> 00:01:40.683
I would like to gather all of that credit

00:01:41.643 --> 00:01:45.772
and dedicate it to the person who's had
the greatest influence on my life.

00:01:46.272 --> 00:01:48.983
My dear friend Ryu Eun-jung.

00:01:50.360 --> 00:01:51.444
I want to thank you.

00:01:52.779 --> 00:01:55.490
…had the greatest influence on my life.
My dear friend…

00:01:59.160 --> 00:02:00.036
Ryu Eun-jung.

00:02:05.792 --> 00:02:06.876
What a load of crap.

00:02:08.837 --> 00:02:10.380
I hate that you're fine.

00:02:13.716 --> 00:02:16.010
I want to see you ruined, like me.

00:03:18.990 --> 00:03:22.911
YOU AND EVERYTHING ELSE

00:03:24.704 --> 00:03:25.747
You severed ties?

00:03:26.247 --> 00:03:27.081
Yes.

00:03:30.877 --> 00:03:31.794
It's just

00:03:32.295 --> 00:03:36.466
the expression "severed ties" is something
you only read about in books.

00:03:38.509 --> 00:03:39.886
Why did you sever ties?

00:03:43.389 --> 00:03:45.266
It's a long story.

00:03:46.392 --> 00:03:47.352
Find anything good?

00:03:49.771 --> 00:03:50.605
No.

00:03:51.814 --> 00:03:53.775
I've been looking hard,

00:03:54.400 --> 00:03:55.902
but no books have blown me away.

00:03:55.985 --> 00:03:57.153
Me neither.

00:03:57.820 --> 00:04:00.698
I've looked through
entire libraries lately,

00:04:00.782 --> 00:04:02.367
but nothing has caught my eye.

00:04:02.450 --> 00:04:03.493
Ms. Ryu.

00:04:06.412 --> 00:04:09.207
What's the story behind
you and Ms. Cheon severing ties?

00:04:17.507 --> 00:04:18.758
Would it work as a script?

00:04:20.301 --> 00:04:23.388
Why not? You saying you severed ties
has me intrigued.

00:04:28.935 --> 00:04:30.687
Thing is, there was no major incident.

00:04:31.729 --> 00:04:35.525
It was just two girls bickering
until they decided to sever ties.

00:04:36.359 --> 00:04:37.860
That's all there is to it.

00:04:37.944 --> 00:04:39.946
But why did you sever ties?

00:04:51.499 --> 00:04:52.375
Who knows?

00:04:58.006 --> 00:04:59.173
How does it feel?

00:05:00.425 --> 00:05:03.011
She said that you had
such a huge influence on her.

00:05:03.094 --> 00:05:05.388
The Cheon Sang-yeon said such a thing.

00:05:05.888 --> 00:05:07.849
Do you like Cheon Sang-yeon?

00:05:11.060 --> 00:05:11.894
Well,

00:05:12.979 --> 00:05:14.522
I don't dislike her.

00:05:15.023 --> 00:05:17.400
Her company tends to make solid movies.

00:05:17.900 --> 00:05:20.778
I wouldn't know.
I haven't seen any of them.

00:05:22.363 --> 00:05:23.573
Even Echoes of Summer?

00:05:25.700 --> 00:05:28.328
Okay, I guess I've seen that one.

00:05:30.246 --> 00:05:32.248
Sounds like
you intentionally avoided them.

00:05:35.335 --> 00:05:37.712
Oh, I don't know.

00:05:39.339 --> 00:05:41.841
Maybe I'm being petty
because she's too successful.

00:05:42.842 --> 00:05:44.886
I guess I can't entirely deny it.

00:05:46.554 --> 00:05:49.098
I don't think
Cheon Sang-yeon deserves the success.

00:05:52.101 --> 00:05:52.935
Why not?

00:05:55.521 --> 00:05:57.106
Do you remember my miniseries?

00:05:58.399 --> 00:05:59.609
Yeong-won and Me.

00:06:01.069 --> 00:06:04.864
The character Cha Yeong-won
was modeled after Cheon Sang-yeon.

00:06:06.199 --> 00:06:07.909
I made her work in advertising,

00:06:07.992 --> 00:06:10.870
but the rest is exactly what happened
with Echoes of Summer

00:06:11.371 --> 00:06:12.413
Echoes of Summer?

00:06:13.247 --> 00:06:14.749
You wrote that?

00:06:16.209 --> 00:06:17.043
Yes.

00:06:17.126 --> 00:06:19.754
Without that movie,
Swallow Pictures wouldn't exist today.

00:06:19.837 --> 00:06:21.172
I developed that story.

00:06:23.466 --> 00:06:25.551
Thinking about it
pisses me off all over again.

00:06:27.178 --> 00:06:28.846
Shall we write a show about it?

00:06:29.722 --> 00:06:31.682
-Rat her out to the world?
-Yes!

00:06:32.683 --> 00:06:33.893
There's no major incident.

00:06:34.477 --> 00:06:37.897
Of course there is. You severed ties!
And she stole Echoes of Summer.

00:06:37.980 --> 00:06:38.981
Maybe you're right.

00:06:48.032 --> 00:06:49.158
Actually…

00:06:51.202 --> 00:06:53.371
I have written a little something.

00:06:53.913 --> 00:06:55.415
About you and Ms. Cheon?

00:06:55.498 --> 00:06:57.125
No, that's not it.

00:06:57.625 --> 00:06:59.127
Do you remember last year

00:07:00.086 --> 00:07:04.173
I told you that I wanted to write about
an elementary school teacher?

00:07:16.394 --> 00:07:19.814
I'm warning you that it's a rough draft.

00:07:20.398 --> 00:07:22.692
Start to finish,
it's just noisy elementary kids.

00:07:23.192 --> 00:07:25.653
Just hand it over. Come on. Don't worry.

00:08:09.655 --> 00:08:12.992
1992, FOURTH GRADE
FIRST DAY OF SECOND SEMESTER

00:08:13.075 --> 00:08:18.456
ILYEONG ELEMENTARY SCHOOL

00:08:40.269 --> 00:08:43.564
CLASS SCHEDULE

00:08:49.654 --> 00:08:50.488
Quiet!

00:08:52.865 --> 00:08:54.283
RYU EUN-JUNG

00:08:58.788 --> 00:09:00.248
Come in.

00:09:00.748 --> 00:09:03.834
Twelve new kids transferred
in a single day.

00:09:05.920 --> 00:09:07.880
Come in. Stand at the front.

00:09:11.968 --> 00:09:15.930
-Attention. Salute.
-Good morning, sir.

00:09:16.430 --> 00:09:17.932
Did you enjoy your break?

00:09:18.015 --> 00:09:19.850
Yes!

00:09:20.351 --> 00:09:22.979
You're not quite sure
what's going on, right?

00:09:23.062 --> 00:09:24.689
Yes!

00:09:25.314 --> 00:09:26.899
The kids who are absent today,

00:09:26.983 --> 00:09:29.402
Sang-uk, Yong-don, Sang-beom, Jeong-ho,

00:09:29.485 --> 00:09:32.530
Geun-su, Eun-i, Mi-jin,
Hyo-jin, and Shin-yeong,

00:09:33.030 --> 00:09:35.533
all transferred
to a different school over break.

00:09:37.785 --> 00:09:40.538
Did you see the new apartment complex
on your way to school?

00:09:40.621 --> 00:09:42.248
Yes!

00:09:42.331 --> 00:09:46.210
These kids have all moved
into those new apartments.

00:09:48.504 --> 00:09:52.049
I'm Shin An-na
from Anyang East Elementary.

00:09:52.133 --> 00:09:53.968
My name is Lee Ji-seon.

00:09:54.051 --> 00:09:55.094
I'm Kim Jeong-ho.

00:09:55.177 --> 00:09:56.178
I'm Seo Jeong-sik.

00:09:56.262 --> 00:09:57.680
My hobby is playing the piano.

00:09:57.763 --> 00:09:59.181
I'm good at arm wrestling.

00:09:59.265 --> 00:10:01.017
It's nice to meet you.

00:10:01.100 --> 00:10:02.435
Nice to meet you.

00:10:06.272 --> 00:10:07.732
It's Sang-yeon's turn.

00:10:08.733 --> 00:10:10.568
Come here. Everyone, listen up.

00:10:14.363 --> 00:10:18.451
Hi, guys. I'm Cheon Sang-yeon,
transferring from Myeongjeong Elementary.

00:10:19.327 --> 00:10:23.164
My mom told me that the "yeon" in my name
means "swallow."

00:10:23.664 --> 00:10:25.207
Swallows are drifters,

00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:27.960
so my dream is to be a deadbeat drifter.

00:10:29.629 --> 00:10:31.505
She wants to be a deadbeat!

00:10:31.589 --> 00:10:36.510
Sang-yeon's grandfather is rather famous.
He was once a government minister.

00:10:36.594 --> 00:10:38.971
Whoa, cool!

00:10:39.055 --> 00:10:42.933
Sang-yeon transferred here
from the best private school in Seoul,

00:10:43.017 --> 00:10:46.103
and while there,
she was an outstanding student.

00:10:46.187 --> 00:10:50.524
So our class has gained a great classmate.

00:10:50.608 --> 00:10:52.068
Round of applause, everyone!

00:10:52.151 --> 00:10:54.779
Wow!

00:10:55.279 --> 00:10:57.156
I think Cheon Sang-yeon is a genius.

00:10:57.239 --> 00:10:58.991
Really? How come?

00:10:59.617 --> 00:11:02.953
In math, she had a contest
with our class president, Kim Kyeong-ho,

00:11:03.454 --> 00:11:04.288
and she won!

00:11:05.164 --> 00:11:07.166
-Guess what they worked on.
-What?

00:11:07.249 --> 00:11:10.419
-A sixth-grade math question.
-A sixth-grade math question?

00:11:10.503 --> 00:11:13.339
The teacher first gave them
a fourth-grade math problem…

00:11:13.422 --> 00:11:16.217
I was subdued and silent at school,

00:11:16.300 --> 00:11:19.387
but outside of school,
I became a total chatterbox.

00:11:19.929 --> 00:11:22.515
He ended up giving them
a fifth-grade question.

00:11:23.432 --> 00:11:25.851
-Thank you, sir.
-Bye, kids.

00:11:30.439 --> 00:11:34.360
Wasn't your class also short on desks
because of the new kids?

00:11:34.443 --> 00:11:36.529
We were three short. What about yours?

00:11:37.029 --> 00:11:39.990
-We were two desks short.
-What did your class do?

00:11:40.574 --> 00:11:43.911
Two of the new transfers don't have desks.

00:11:44.412 --> 00:11:47.164
It would be nice
if someone volunteered to give up theirs.

00:11:47.248 --> 00:11:51.168
The teacher asked the boys
if any of them would give up their seats,

00:11:51.669 --> 00:11:52.962
and Kyeong-ho offered first.

00:11:53.045 --> 00:11:56.549
-I will.
-I will!

00:11:56.632 --> 00:11:58.426
Then all the other boys offered,

00:11:58.509 --> 00:12:00.469
and the teacher decided…

00:12:02.346 --> 00:12:06.726
Alrighty, then. Let's see who'll be
so kind as to give up their seats.

00:12:06.809 --> 00:12:08.811
Let's see. Our volunteers will be

00:12:08.894 --> 00:12:11.021
Go Yeong-rok and Lee Jeong-kyu!

00:12:11.814 --> 00:12:14.066
What? Go Yeong-rok and Lee Jeong-kyu?

00:12:14.567 --> 00:12:16.736
Even though Kyeong-ho offered first?

00:12:16.819 --> 00:12:17.820
I already told you.

00:12:18.320 --> 00:12:22.283
My teacher never makes
kids like Kyeong-ho do grunt work.

00:12:22.783 --> 00:12:24.577
Just the kids from our neighborhood.

00:12:25.286 --> 00:12:27.371
What did they do without desks?

00:12:27.955 --> 00:12:31.250
To read large numbers,
we group the digits in sets of four.

00:12:31.333 --> 00:12:34.879
Six, seven, eight, nine,
and two, three, four, five… like this.

00:12:34.962 --> 00:12:38.007
Now label the first three digits
as thousands, hundreds, and tens.

00:12:38.090 --> 00:12:38.966
The whole day?

00:12:39.049 --> 00:12:42.136
The whole day. What about you guys?

00:12:42.803 --> 00:12:44.096
We were all seated.

00:12:44.180 --> 00:12:45.556
Yes, ma'am!

00:12:45.639 --> 00:12:46.515
Now, listen up.

00:12:46.599 --> 00:12:50.352
A mixture is when more than two matters
are blended together.

00:12:50.436 --> 00:12:52.563
There are solid and liquid mixtures…

00:12:53.105 --> 00:12:53.981
On the vaulting horse?

00:12:54.732 --> 00:12:57.777
Yeah. The teacher and the class monitor
brought it to the classroom.

00:12:58.527 --> 00:13:00.613
You're so lucky you have a nice teacher.

00:13:01.113 --> 00:13:03.324
My teacher always plays favorites.

00:13:07.328 --> 00:13:10.122
It's my mom. I'll catch you later. Mom!

00:13:46.700 --> 00:13:48.536
Mom. Kim Mi-jin transferred schools.

00:13:48.619 --> 00:13:50.579
Really? Where to?

00:13:51.080 --> 00:13:55.709
I'm not sure. The teacher listed everyone
who transferred, including Mi-jin.

00:13:56.544 --> 00:13:58.087
-But…
-Here, drink this.

00:13:58.170 --> 00:13:59.380
For me? Again?

00:13:59.463 --> 00:14:00.881
-I'm just so grateful.
-Thanks.

00:14:00.965 --> 00:14:03.717
-Can I have the keys?
-The keys…

00:14:03.801 --> 00:14:05.469
The keys… Here they are.

00:14:06.262 --> 00:14:07.721
Thank you!

00:14:10.266 --> 00:14:11.100
Mom.

00:14:11.600 --> 00:14:14.895
Mi-jin didn't return my comic book
before transferring.

00:14:14.979 --> 00:14:15.813
And?

00:14:16.397 --> 00:14:19.275
And I'd borrowed it
from the truck bookstore man.

00:14:19.775 --> 00:14:20.609
And?

00:14:21.110 --> 00:14:23.863
I need to pay him for the comic book.
Can I have 1,700 won?

00:14:25.155 --> 00:14:27.950
Is that why you followed me here?

00:14:28.033 --> 00:14:28.868
Yes.

00:14:32.037 --> 00:14:35.124
Don't you have any homework
now that school has started?

00:14:35.624 --> 00:14:37.751
Twelve kids transferred to my class today.

00:14:37.835 --> 00:14:39.712
-Twelve kids?
-Yeah.

00:14:39.795 --> 00:14:42.798
There's this new kid
named Cheon Sang-yeon.

00:14:42.882 --> 00:14:46.010
Apparently, her grandad was a minister.
That means he's high up, right?

00:14:46.093 --> 00:14:48.596
High up, indeed.
What was he a minister of?

00:14:49.096 --> 00:14:51.640
I don't know. Just a famous minister.

00:14:53.684 --> 00:14:57.479
Mom, whose house is this? How come you're…

00:15:00.524 --> 00:15:02.610
-Do you like it?
-Yeah.

00:15:04.278 --> 00:15:05.738
The curtains are already up.

00:15:06.447 --> 00:15:07.406
How pretty.

00:15:12.995 --> 00:15:14.872
I have to work, so look around.

00:15:16.415 --> 00:15:18.167
-I can look around?
-Why not?

00:15:24.006 --> 00:15:28.010
That was the first time
I ever stepped inside an apartment.

00:15:30.721 --> 00:15:31.931
That apartment

00:15:33.265 --> 00:15:34.642
was spacious,

00:15:35.309 --> 00:15:36.393
spacious,

00:15:36.894 --> 00:15:38.187
and spacious.

00:15:38.729 --> 00:15:40.481
It was just so spacious.

00:16:24.566 --> 00:16:27.903
Mom! There's a bathroom
inside the bedroom!

00:16:27.987 --> 00:16:28.821
And?

00:16:29.655 --> 00:16:33.951
Not the one out there.
There's another bathroom in this room!

00:16:34.034 --> 00:16:37.621
I know. This place has two bathrooms.

00:16:39.748 --> 00:16:41.250
There are two bathrooms?

00:16:42.876 --> 00:16:45.713
How can a single house have two bathrooms?

00:16:45.796 --> 00:16:46.755
All these places do.

00:16:47.798 --> 00:16:48.799
They all do?

00:16:49.967 --> 00:16:51.010
Love at first sight.

00:16:51.885 --> 00:16:54.179
-It was totally love at first sight.
-Mom.

00:16:55.139 --> 00:16:57.641
-Who lives in places like these?
-Who knows?

00:16:58.684 --> 00:17:00.853
The security guard says
it's a family of four,

00:17:00.936 --> 00:17:03.814
so it's probably two children
and their parents.

00:17:05.274 --> 00:17:06.358
Two children…

00:17:07.901 --> 00:17:10.195
If you're bored,
why not help your mom out?

00:17:10.279 --> 00:17:12.156
I'll give you 1,700 won.

00:17:12.656 --> 00:17:13.532
Really?

00:18:01.455 --> 00:18:05.334
YOU'RE SO LUCKY

00:18:21.058 --> 00:18:23.727
On Saturday, there was a vote
for class president.

00:18:23.811 --> 00:18:25.229
BALLOT

00:18:25.312 --> 00:18:28.148
In a democracy,
who you vote for is a secret.

00:18:37.116 --> 00:18:39.409
CHEON SANG-YEON

00:18:39.493 --> 00:18:40.744
Cheon Sang-yeon.

00:18:41.912 --> 00:18:44.873
SECOND SEMESTER CLASS PRESIDENT ELECTION
CHEON SANG-YEON, JEONG NAM-HYEON

00:18:44.957 --> 00:18:46.250
Cheon Sang-yeon.

00:18:48.210 --> 00:18:49.628
Cheon Sang-yeon.

00:18:55.008 --> 00:18:57.010
-Jeong Nam-hyeon.
-Huh?

00:18:57.094 --> 00:18:59.346
Nam-hyeon, did you vote for yourself?

00:19:00.389 --> 00:19:01.765
I did not!

00:19:01.849 --> 00:19:04.476
-He totally voted for himself!
-He totally did!

00:19:04.560 --> 00:19:07.187
When the teacher isn't here,
you're in charge.

00:19:07.271 --> 00:19:09.398
Make sure the kids aren't chattering.

00:19:09.481 --> 00:19:12.276
And if they don't listen to you,
you can hit them with this.

00:19:12.359 --> 00:19:13.652
Kyeong-ho's right.

00:19:14.153 --> 00:19:16.613
Who's in charge when I'm not here?

00:19:16.697 --> 00:19:19.032
-The class president!
-Correct.

00:19:19.116 --> 00:19:20.284
A round of applause.

00:19:38.510 --> 00:19:39.636
I'll help you with this.

00:19:39.720 --> 00:19:42.472
-Sorry?
-Hello. I'm the Seoul Milk lady.

00:19:42.556 --> 00:19:43.640
That's quite all right.

00:19:43.724 --> 00:19:47.352
Milk and newspaper delivery folks
promote sales like this,

00:19:47.436 --> 00:19:48.937
so no pressure.

00:19:49.438 --> 00:19:50.856
I just feel bad.

00:19:50.939 --> 00:19:54.193
If you do, spare me
ten minutes of your time later.

00:19:54.276 --> 00:19:55.903
You'll see it yourself,

00:19:55.986 --> 00:19:58.488
but you don't need to clean
the sink and shelves.

00:19:58.572 --> 00:20:00.782
I wiped everything down
with a sterile cloth.

00:20:01.283 --> 00:20:02.743
When did you do all that?

00:20:03.410 --> 00:20:04.828
Please be careful.

00:20:04.912 --> 00:20:06.747
-Seventh floor, right?
-Yes.

00:20:07.372 --> 00:20:09.750
You always let him have his way!

00:20:11.835 --> 00:20:14.254
-Help me with this.
-Put everything inside.

00:20:15.088 --> 00:20:17.883
How pretty. Is she your daughter?

00:20:18.467 --> 00:20:21.678
Yes. She's upset
because she prefers her brother's room.

00:20:22.804 --> 00:20:25.015
-What grade is she in?
-Fourth.

00:20:25.515 --> 00:20:26.725
Ilyeong Elementary?

00:20:26.808 --> 00:20:29.228
Yes. She made the transfer last week.

00:20:29.728 --> 00:20:32.272
She wouldn't be in class five, would she?

00:20:32.773 --> 00:20:33.774
Why do you ask?

00:20:35.234 --> 00:20:37.152
The homeroom teacher is rather…

00:20:38.654 --> 00:20:40.280
Why? What are they like?

00:20:40.364 --> 00:20:43.200
I hear they treat children
based on their family's wealth.

00:20:43.283 --> 00:20:46.245
One day, they were short on desks
because of the new transfers,

00:20:46.328 --> 00:20:49.539
and the two poorest kids
were told to sit on the floor.

00:20:49.623 --> 00:20:51.959
-For the entire day, no less.
-Oh dear.

00:20:52.793 --> 00:20:56.588
How do you know such things?

00:20:56.672 --> 00:20:58.548
My kid told me.

00:20:58.632 --> 00:21:01.343
She must have thought it was unfair.

00:21:01.426 --> 00:21:03.845
Your child must be smart. What's her name?

00:21:04.471 --> 00:21:06.640
It's Eun-jung. Ryu Eun-jung.

00:21:13.730 --> 00:21:14.731
Stop it.

00:21:18.944 --> 00:21:19.778
Cut it out.

00:21:21.822 --> 00:21:22.823
Keep it down.

00:21:25.659 --> 00:21:27.744
-I told you to stop it.
-Hey, you.

00:21:29.454 --> 00:21:30.330
Come up here.

00:21:32.249 --> 00:21:36.628
It's just… Kim Hyeon-tae keeps kicking
my art project.

00:21:36.712 --> 00:21:37.671
Kim Hyeon-tae too.

00:21:37.754 --> 00:21:40.173
Me? But I didn't say anything.

00:21:49.558 --> 00:21:53.645
Honestly, I wasn't trying to talk.
Kim Hyeon-tae kept kicking my project--

00:21:53.729 --> 00:21:57.065
Ryu Eun-jung. If the class president
tells you to come up, you listen.

00:21:57.149 --> 00:21:59.151
Would you talk back to the teacher?

00:22:16.418 --> 00:22:17.336
Palms out.

00:22:20.088 --> 00:22:22.924
-You too.
-I told you I didn't say anything.

00:22:25.635 --> 00:22:27.179
She hits really hard.

00:22:33.310 --> 00:22:34.561
Hey, Ryu Eun-jung.

00:23:17.396 --> 00:23:19.439
Mommy's home.

00:23:21.691 --> 00:23:23.235
Did you kids have a good day?

00:23:32.119 --> 00:23:32.953
What's wrong?

00:23:33.036 --> 00:23:34.287
Is something up?

00:23:34.788 --> 00:23:35.664
No.

00:23:39.334 --> 00:23:40.168
Let me see you.

00:23:41.461 --> 00:23:43.797
So something is up!

00:23:45.549 --> 00:23:46.883
I told you. It's nothing.

00:23:47.384 --> 00:23:50.137
Who was it? Who upset my daughter?

00:23:50.220 --> 00:23:52.806
Mom, the thing is,

00:23:53.306 --> 00:23:55.559
earlier at school, Cheon Sang-yeon, she…

00:23:55.642 --> 00:23:58.311
I was so upset and humiliated
by that incident

00:23:58.895 --> 00:24:01.148
that I held a grudge for a very long time.

00:24:02.065 --> 00:24:04.943
Even after we moved up a grade
and were put in separate classes,

00:24:05.026 --> 00:24:07.946
just seeing Cheon Sang-yeon
triggered an urge to fight.

00:24:11.241 --> 00:24:14.494
As my grades improved,
and I made more friends in fifth grade,

00:24:14.578 --> 00:24:15.871
my personality changed.

00:24:15.954 --> 00:24:17.080
Catch it!

00:24:17.164 --> 00:24:19.666
Wait, time out! You stepped on the line.

00:24:19.749 --> 00:24:21.751
-I didn't.
-Basically, I became cocky.

00:24:23.962 --> 00:24:25.839
She stepped on the line right here.

00:24:27.799 --> 00:24:29.885
-Let's just play.
-I didn't step on the line.

00:24:29.968 --> 00:24:31.761
Hurry up.

00:24:33.763 --> 00:24:35.015
Come on, try harder.

00:24:35.098 --> 00:24:36.391
Throw it over here.

00:24:37.309 --> 00:24:38.268
-Nice one.
-Catch it!

00:24:41.396 --> 00:24:42.772
-Are you okay?
-Are you hurt?

00:24:42.856 --> 00:24:44.149
Are you all right?

00:24:44.649 --> 00:24:47.194
Ryu Eun-jung!
Why did you aim for her head?

00:24:47.277 --> 00:24:50.906
-She threw it at her on purpose.
-Why would I do that?

00:24:50.989 --> 00:24:53.867
You've only been attacking Sang-yeon.

00:24:53.950 --> 00:24:57.996
That's because Cheon Sang-yeon's good.
You were all attacking Eun-jung.

00:24:58.497 --> 00:25:01.500
-It's dodgeball. People get hit.
-But she threw it at her head!

00:25:01.583 --> 00:25:04.252
It really hurts to get hit in the head.

00:25:04.336 --> 00:25:05.337
You can die!

00:25:05.420 --> 00:25:07.506
-No, you can't.
-Yes, you can!

00:25:08.298 --> 00:25:09.174
The teacher's here.

00:25:10.008 --> 00:25:11.218
Everyone freeze.

00:25:11.801 --> 00:25:15.222
Why are you fighting
instead of playing dodgeball?

00:25:34.157 --> 00:25:35.158
You're here.

00:25:43.166 --> 00:25:44.417
Hello.

00:25:44.918 --> 00:25:46.294
Hi, Eun-jung.

00:25:48.046 --> 00:25:51.925
It happened while playing dodgeball,
so Eun-jung should apologize.

00:25:52.759 --> 00:25:55.053
Why don't you two shake hands and make up?

00:25:58.557 --> 00:25:59.391
I'm sorry.

00:26:06.022 --> 00:26:08.775
Class matches often get
a little out of hand.

00:26:09.359 --> 00:26:12.237
Sang-yeon,
stop being dramatic and make up.

00:26:17.367 --> 00:26:19.035
Admit that you did it on purpose.

00:26:20.036 --> 00:26:22.080
-I didn't.
-As if!

00:26:22.622 --> 00:26:24.457
You attacked me from the start.

00:26:26.084 --> 00:26:27.794
It still wasn't on purpose.

00:26:29.879 --> 00:26:32.299
You mean it wasn't intentional, right?

00:26:35.844 --> 00:26:38.680
I didn't mean to throw it at her head.

00:26:38.763 --> 00:26:39.598
Of course you did!

00:26:40.557 --> 00:26:41.641
Cheon Sang-yeon.

00:26:42.934 --> 00:26:44.853
You don't even know what happened.

00:26:45.395 --> 00:26:46.855
She did it on purpose!

00:26:48.690 --> 00:26:49.983
Cheon Sang-yeon.

00:26:59.701 --> 00:27:00.619
Mom?

00:27:01.119 --> 00:27:01.995
Yes?

00:27:02.078 --> 00:27:02.912
Today,

00:27:04.414 --> 00:27:08.126
we played dodgeball in gym class,
and I threw the ball at Sang-yeon.

00:27:08.627 --> 00:27:10.754
It hit her head, so she went to the nurse.

00:27:10.837 --> 00:27:13.423
To the nurse? How hard did you hit her?

00:27:13.506 --> 00:27:15.925
I didn't hit her.
The ball did. It was dodgeball.

00:27:22.223 --> 00:27:23.058
But

00:27:23.850 --> 00:27:25.185
it did hit her hard.

00:27:25.268 --> 00:27:27.812
Well, is she okay?

00:27:28.396 --> 00:27:34.277
Yeah. She was all right soon after,
but I can't tell if I did it on purpose.

00:27:36.196 --> 00:27:39.658
Even though I wasn't sure,
I denied it to the teacher.

00:27:40.492 --> 00:27:41.660
Does that count as lying?

00:27:42.535 --> 00:27:44.037
Who knows?

00:27:46.915 --> 00:27:49.125
Are you really not sure?

00:27:58.635 --> 00:28:02.722
Mom, Ms. Yoon came
to the nurse's office earlier.

00:28:03.390 --> 00:28:04.808
My writing teacher.

00:28:05.392 --> 00:28:07.310
-Really?
-Yeah.

00:28:07.394 --> 00:28:09.896
I wonder why she was there at all.

00:28:09.979 --> 00:28:11.523
What did she say?

00:28:12.107 --> 00:28:17.696
She told Sang-yeon to make up with me,
but Sang-yeon talked back to her and left.

00:28:17.779 --> 00:28:20.490
-She said, "You don't know what happened."
-Really?

00:28:20.990 --> 00:28:22.659
She spoke rudely to the teacher?

00:28:22.742 --> 00:28:23.952
Exactly.

00:28:29.207 --> 00:28:31.042
-Move your legs.
-Don't touch me.

00:28:33.044 --> 00:28:36.047
I don't know. I really don't.

00:28:36.673 --> 00:28:40.176
-Write about it in your journal.
-I wouldn't know what to write.

00:28:40.260 --> 00:28:42.595
Write that you don't know!

00:28:44.097 --> 00:28:46.641
Tomorrow's Wednesday!
You have your extracurricular class.

00:28:52.230 --> 00:28:56.192
THEME: THE MOST IMPORTANT PROMISE
I EVER MADE

00:29:01.865 --> 00:29:06.327
For my extracurricular class,
I was in Ms. Yoon's writing class.

00:29:08.788 --> 00:29:11.374
Now that I think about it,
my personality changed

00:29:12.125 --> 00:29:13.418
on that day.

00:29:18.465 --> 00:29:20.341
Raise your hand if you don't have a mom.

00:29:20.425 --> 00:29:21.468
1 YEAR AGO

00:29:21.551 --> 00:29:23.303
I'd wanted to cry that day

00:29:23.970 --> 00:29:26.890
because that morning,
there had been a family background check.

00:29:26.973 --> 00:29:28.224
No one.

00:29:28.725 --> 00:29:30.602
Raise your hand if you don't have a dad.

00:29:32.771 --> 00:29:34.731
-You don't live with your dad?
-I don't.

00:29:35.356 --> 00:29:37.567
-Your name?
-Lee Han-jun.

00:29:37.650 --> 00:29:39.694
Hey. You don't have a dad either.

00:29:40.487 --> 00:29:42.530
He's only asking the new kids.

00:29:45.116 --> 00:29:46.951
Anyone else without a dad?

00:29:47.035 --> 00:29:48.661
Ryu Eun-jung doesn't have one!

00:29:49.829 --> 00:29:51.331
She's always been at this school.

00:29:51.414 --> 00:29:53.792
I'm just asking about the new transfers.

00:29:59.130 --> 00:30:02.675
Let's move on to your parents' education
if there's no one else.

00:30:03.593 --> 00:30:05.553
Whose parents only finished
elementary school?

00:30:06.763 --> 00:30:09.265
-Goodbye.
-See you next class.

00:30:09.849 --> 00:30:10.683
Goodbye.

00:30:15.855 --> 00:30:16.898
Eun-jung?

00:30:18.358 --> 00:30:19.651
Hello.

00:30:21.277 --> 00:30:24.948
This is quite heavy.
Would you mind helping me?

00:30:26.157 --> 00:30:26.991
Sure.

00:30:30.620 --> 00:30:31.538
Thank you.

00:30:35.416 --> 00:30:39.128
I was shocked that she knew my name.

00:30:40.004 --> 00:30:42.423
Other teachers didn't know my name

00:30:42.924 --> 00:30:45.176
because I was one of those kids
who blended in.

00:30:45.677 --> 00:30:47.595
I was invisible.

00:30:58.189 --> 00:30:59.357
All done!

00:30:59.858 --> 00:31:01.818
You've been so helpful. Why don't you sit?

00:31:01.901 --> 00:31:02.735
Okay.

00:31:14.330 --> 00:31:15.707
Thank you for helping me.

00:31:21.004 --> 00:31:22.630
Why don't you take off your bag?

00:31:24.424 --> 00:31:25.258
Drink up.

00:31:46.154 --> 00:31:47.530
Eun-jung.

00:31:49.782 --> 00:31:51.367
You don't have a dad, do you?

00:31:55.455 --> 00:31:56.289
No, I don't.

00:31:58.041 --> 00:32:00.335
Are you shocked that I knew?

00:32:02.253 --> 00:32:05.256
I was passing in the hallway
and happened to overhear.

00:32:10.887 --> 00:32:14.682
My dad also passed away when I was young.

00:32:18.186 --> 00:32:20.521
He passed away when I was in sixth grade.

00:32:21.022 --> 00:32:23.191
How old were you when yours passed?

00:32:25.485 --> 00:32:26.694
I was eight.

00:32:29.614 --> 00:32:30.782
I see.

00:32:32.200 --> 00:32:33.910
You must have been so heartbroken.

00:32:36.245 --> 00:32:38.039
It was like that for me too.

00:32:39.415 --> 00:32:43.127
I felt so sad whenever I missed my dad.

00:32:45.421 --> 00:32:46.631
Do you feel the same?

00:32:49.342 --> 00:32:50.176
Yes.

00:33:10.613 --> 00:33:11.781
Thank you.

00:33:13.533 --> 00:33:15.118
Go on and blow your nose.

00:33:29.424 --> 00:33:30.258
Eun-jung.

00:33:31.050 --> 00:33:35.638
I really wanted to tell you this.

00:33:37.765 --> 00:33:41.269
Whether it's not having a dad or a mom,

00:33:42.228 --> 00:33:46.399
it's sad not being able
to see the ones you love.

00:33:48.818 --> 00:33:50.611
Yet, for some reason,

00:33:51.112 --> 00:33:54.907
when I was younger,
I felt ashamed about not having a dad.

00:33:57.410 --> 00:34:01.247
I didn't feel that way when I was alone,
but in front of others,

00:34:02.248 --> 00:34:03.708
I think I felt embarrassed.

00:34:07.503 --> 00:34:11.090
But now I think of it this way.

00:34:16.429 --> 00:34:17.513
Look here.

00:34:25.313 --> 00:34:29.942
This is the space
you hold in your heart for your dad.

00:34:30.860 --> 00:34:34.989
Your dad's not with you now,
so it's empty, and that makes you sad.

00:34:36.657 --> 00:34:37.575
Yes.

00:34:37.658 --> 00:34:43.372
But it's up to you to decide
what to fill this space with.

00:34:44.165 --> 00:34:45.708
If you, Eun-jung,

00:34:46.334 --> 00:34:47.627
decide to fill this space

00:34:49.128 --> 00:34:50.338
like this,

00:34:50.838 --> 00:34:53.966
you could fill it up with goodness.

00:34:55.051 --> 00:34:56.260
There. It's full.

00:34:58.262 --> 00:35:00.556
Once you grow up, you can say,

00:35:01.057 --> 00:35:03.101
"Not having a dad made me sad,

00:35:03.601 --> 00:35:06.979
but I filled his space with these things,

00:35:07.063 --> 00:35:12.026
which made me the person I am today."

00:35:13.611 --> 00:35:18.908
Don't you think that would make your dad
proud as he looks down on you?

00:35:19.450 --> 00:35:20.284
Yes.

00:35:24.580 --> 00:35:27.416
On days when you're sad, write a journal.

00:35:27.917 --> 00:35:31.254
Not the sort of journal
you write for homework,

00:35:31.337 --> 00:35:34.298
but about how you really feel.

00:35:35.633 --> 00:35:36.467
Okay.

00:35:53.860 --> 00:35:57.780
Hand in your work if you're finished.
If not, finish it by tomorrow.

00:35:58.281 --> 00:36:01.409
And don't forget to collect your journal
if you handed it in.

00:36:01.492 --> 00:36:03.077
-Yes, ma'am.
-Park Yeon-jin?

00:36:06.414 --> 00:36:07.248
Eun-jung?

00:36:08.624 --> 00:36:09.458
Here.

00:36:11.085 --> 00:36:14.046
-Next, Sang-hyeok.
-Thank you.

00:36:19.010 --> 00:36:20.094
Bye.

