the base sides of the parallelogram,

00:38:31.642 --> 00:38:33.436
we can calculate the distance between…

00:38:35.688 --> 00:38:38.316
Ryu Eun-jung,
I heard that you deliver milk.

00:38:40.192 --> 00:38:41.027
What?

00:38:41.110 --> 00:38:42.445
Who delivers what?

00:38:42.945 --> 00:38:44.947
Ryu Eun-jung. She delivers milk.

00:38:46.073 --> 00:38:48.159
-Is that true?
-No.

00:38:49.201 --> 00:38:50.953
I don't. I was just helping my mom.

00:38:51.037 --> 00:38:52.455
Yeah, by delivering milk.

00:38:54.457 --> 00:38:57.001
Didn't you hear her say
she was helping her mom?

00:39:00.087 --> 00:39:01.380
Kim Seong-kwon.

00:39:02.840 --> 00:39:05.217
-He's in class one, isn't he?
-Yeah.

00:39:06.010 --> 00:39:06.844
Why?

00:39:07.386 --> 00:39:09.847
It was clear
that Cheon Sang-yeon had told him.

00:39:10.931 --> 00:39:13.100
Cheon Sang-yeon was also in class one.

00:39:13.184 --> 00:39:15.478
Why are you telling kids
that I deliver milk?

00:39:15.978 --> 00:39:18.022
-I did?
-Yeah!

00:39:18.522 --> 00:39:20.441
I helped my mom, who had hurt her leg.

00:39:21.025 --> 00:39:22.651
Why would you start such a rumor?

00:39:23.861 --> 00:39:25.321
I didn't start any rumors.

00:39:25.404 --> 00:39:28.074
Then why is Seong-kwon from your class
teasing me about it?

00:39:28.157 --> 00:39:30.534
How would I know? I didn't tell him.

00:39:36.624 --> 00:39:37.625
I should ask you.

00:39:38.584 --> 00:39:40.336
Why do you have it out for me?

00:39:41.504 --> 00:39:43.422
-I do not.
-Admit it!

00:39:43.506 --> 00:39:47.301
You attack only me in dodgeball.
You even hit me with the ball.

00:39:47.385 --> 00:39:48.469
I didn't hit you.

00:39:48.552 --> 00:39:50.304
It sure hurt.

00:39:51.097 --> 00:39:54.058
-If it hurt, it means you hit me.
-You hit me first!

00:39:54.558 --> 00:39:55.393
I did?

00:39:58.229 --> 00:39:59.563
-When?
-In fourth grade!

00:39:59.647 --> 00:40:02.483
You called me to the front
and hit me with the teacher's rod.

00:40:05.945 --> 00:40:07.196
That was you?

00:40:07.279 --> 00:40:09.156
Yeah, that was me, okay?

00:40:09.740 --> 00:40:12.618
I wasn't chattering that day.
Kim Hyeon-tae kept goofing off.

00:40:13.119 --> 00:40:16.622
Plus, my mom says it's ridiculous
for a student to hit another student.

00:40:20.709 --> 00:40:21.544
Okay.

00:40:22.628 --> 00:40:25.965
I get it.
If you're so upset, you can hit me too.

00:40:27.633 --> 00:40:28.467
What?

00:40:28.551 --> 00:40:31.011
I said hit me. Then we'd be even.

00:40:32.388 --> 00:40:33.222
Hit me with this.

00:40:35.933 --> 00:40:36.767
Hit me.

00:40:36.851 --> 00:40:38.394
Do you think I won't?

00:40:38.477 --> 00:40:39.937
I'm telling you to go ahead.

00:40:40.020 --> 00:40:41.772
-You're seriously--
-Go on, hit me!

00:40:49.113 --> 00:40:50.906
Hey, are you crying?

00:40:50.990 --> 00:40:52.491
As if I'd cry!

00:40:53.200 --> 00:40:56.162
-Why won't you hit me?
-Do you know how much this would hurt?

00:40:58.330 --> 00:41:00.166
This is harder than wood.

00:41:12.636 --> 00:41:15.931
You're the one who couldn't hit me,
so don't blame me.

00:41:19.810 --> 00:41:21.187
You really didn't tell anyone?

00:41:21.770 --> 00:41:22.855
I didn't.

00:41:23.355 --> 00:41:24.690
Swear on it.

00:41:24.773 --> 00:41:25.608
I swear.

00:41:32.907 --> 00:41:33.949
Hey, Ryu Eun-jung!

00:41:38.120 --> 00:41:39.622
You may not have hit me,

00:41:40.122 --> 00:41:42.082
but I was already punished
for hitting you.

00:41:44.835 --> 00:41:46.170
I didn't know it was you,

00:41:47.379 --> 00:41:49.924
but my mom hit me
for hitting you that day.

00:41:53.594 --> 00:41:55.012
My mom's Yoon Hyun-sook.

00:41:58.098 --> 00:41:59.183
Ms. Yoon?

00:41:59.808 --> 00:42:00.643
Yeah.

00:42:23.415 --> 00:42:24.959
Mom, guess what.

00:42:25.042 --> 00:42:27.503
Cheon Sang-yeon is Ms. Yoon's daughter.

00:42:27.586 --> 00:42:28.629
Really?

00:42:28.712 --> 00:42:31.715
Yeah. Last year, Ms. Yoon
was the homeroom teacher for--

00:42:31.799 --> 00:42:34.677
I know. The homeroom teacher
for the class next to yours.

00:42:34.760 --> 00:42:36.720
This year,
she teaches extracurricular classes.

00:42:36.804 --> 00:42:39.139
Yeah. It turns out that
she's Cheon Sang-yeon's mom.

00:42:39.223 --> 00:42:41.308
Really?

00:42:45.437 --> 00:42:47.815
Hold up. Did you already know?

00:42:48.524 --> 00:42:50.150
Yeah, I already knew.

00:42:50.234 --> 00:42:51.610
How did you know?

00:42:52.194 --> 00:42:53.737
She buys her milk from me.

00:42:56.031 --> 00:42:57.408
It's hot. Move your hands.

00:43:05.249 --> 00:43:06.375
-Mom.
-Yeah?

00:43:06.458 --> 00:43:09.420
Was it you who told her I got hit?

00:43:09.503 --> 00:43:10.337
Yeah.

00:43:10.838 --> 00:43:12.590
I went to collect their milk money

00:43:12.673 --> 00:43:14.800
and told her your class president hit you.

00:43:14.883 --> 00:43:17.344
She was utterly shocked and apologized,

00:43:17.428 --> 00:43:19.430
saying her daughter
is your class president.

00:43:20.097 --> 00:43:21.390
Why didn't you tell me?

00:43:22.391 --> 00:43:23.809
She told me not to.

00:43:24.977 --> 00:43:26.854
She teaches the class next to yours

00:43:26.937 --> 00:43:29.481
and no one at school
knows she's her daughter.

00:43:30.232 --> 00:43:31.817
Don't tell the kids.

00:43:32.526 --> 00:43:33.360
Okay.

00:43:35.404 --> 00:43:39.408
Apparently,
Ms. Yoon hit Sang-yeon for hitting me.

00:43:40.242 --> 00:43:41.744
-She did?
-Yes.

00:43:43.787 --> 00:43:48.042
Cheon Sang-yeon's transferring next month.
Can't you be friends until then?

00:43:48.125 --> 00:43:50.961
You want me to be friends
with Cheon Sang-yeon?

00:43:51.045 --> 00:43:52.046
Yeah.

00:43:53.922 --> 00:43:55.049
How tasty.

00:43:55.132 --> 00:43:59.219
The thought of being friends
with Sang-yeon was so absurd

00:44:00.220 --> 00:44:02.723
because Cheon Sang-yeon
was just too smart.

00:44:03.974 --> 00:44:06.185
It was absurd
because she had such fair skin,

00:44:06.268 --> 00:44:08.103
her grandad was a government minister,

00:44:08.896 --> 00:44:14.485
and her mom, Ms. Yoon,
was my favorite teacher.

00:44:15.736 --> 00:44:19.031
It was also because of Son Jun-ho,
my desk buddy.

00:44:20.532 --> 00:44:21.700
Hey, Ryu Eun-jung.

00:44:23.243 --> 00:44:24.244
Here.

00:44:26.955 --> 00:44:30.334
Son Jun-ho was very popular.

00:44:31.835 --> 00:44:34.797
Just this once. Please tell me.

00:44:36.674 --> 00:44:38.300
Who does Son Jun-ho like?

00:44:39.259 --> 00:44:42.680
I'm not sure, but I don't think it's you.

00:44:49.645 --> 00:44:51.397
Still, deliver this to him.

00:45:01.740 --> 00:45:04.410
-Go Na-mi told me to give you this.
-Go Na-mi?

00:45:18.590 --> 00:45:21.593
If I'm honest, I liked Son Jun-ho too.

00:45:25.180 --> 00:45:27.433
Do you guys want to choose desk buddies?

00:45:28.183 --> 00:45:30.310
You'll soon be saying goodbye,
which is a shame.

00:45:32.646 --> 00:45:33.897
Don't you guys want to?

00:45:34.523 --> 00:45:36.400
Everyone in my class was keen.

00:45:36.483 --> 00:45:38.902
We are too.
Let us choose our buddies, please!

00:45:38.986 --> 00:45:40.738
-Yes, please.
-Please let us choose.

00:45:40.821 --> 00:45:41.655
Okay.

00:45:42.781 --> 00:45:45.367
-The process was simple.
-Jeong-sik?

00:45:46.285 --> 00:45:47.327
Lee Eun-jae.

00:45:47.411 --> 00:45:50.873
Boys would call out the name of the girl
they wanted to sit with,

00:45:50.956 --> 00:45:54.126
and the girl would get the final say.

00:45:54.209 --> 00:45:55.461
Seo Jeong-sik.

00:45:59.798 --> 00:46:00.799
Jun-ho?

00:46:00.883 --> 00:46:04.178
When it was Jun-ho's turn,
I was nervous for no reason.

00:46:04.803 --> 00:46:07.473
It was obvious who he would pick.

00:46:08.056 --> 00:46:10.851
Son Jun-ho would pick Cheon Sang-yeon.

00:46:11.560 --> 00:46:12.394
Ryu Eun-jung.

00:46:13.312 --> 00:46:15.063
Eun-jung?

00:46:22.571 --> 00:46:25.282
-See you all in our next class.
-Thank you!

00:46:25.365 --> 00:46:28.577
I could feel
the kids looking at me differently.

00:46:29.578 --> 00:46:31.079
All of them except one.

00:46:31.914 --> 00:46:33.957
-How could this happen?
-It's not a big deal.

00:46:36.668 --> 00:46:41.215
Then Cheon Sang-yeon transferred
to the new school across from ours.

00:46:54.269 --> 00:46:55.354
Can we talk?

00:47:06.698 --> 00:47:08.367
What? A love letter?

00:47:08.450 --> 00:47:13.539
Yeah. The day before she transferred,
Jun-ho wrote Sang-yeon a love letter.

00:47:15.249 --> 00:47:17.626
I heard that he cried
while giving it to her.

00:47:18.460 --> 00:47:19.294
He cried?

00:47:19.837 --> 00:47:22.506
Because it's so tragic
to part with the one he loves.

00:47:23.298 --> 00:47:25.467
-Right…
-Right?

00:47:26.009 --> 00:47:26.969
Come on.

00:47:27.052 --> 00:47:29.429
Now isn't the time
to be sitting here like this.

00:47:30.138 --> 00:47:31.265
What else should I do?

00:47:36.854 --> 00:47:38.230
Hey, Son Jun-ho!

00:47:39.606 --> 00:47:40.941
Tell us the truth.

00:47:41.024 --> 00:47:43.527
Did you really write Sang-yeon
a love letter?

00:47:44.027 --> 00:47:45.279
-Sang-yeon?
-A love letter?

00:47:45.362 --> 00:47:47.489
-The one who transferred?
-Really?

00:47:47.573 --> 00:47:49.825
-What are you talking about?
-Is it true?

00:47:51.451 --> 00:47:52.828
Do I have to answer?

00:47:52.911 --> 00:47:55.622
Unbelievable.
Of course you have to answer!

00:47:55.706 --> 00:47:59.626
If you wrote Sang-yeon a love letter,
it means that you like her.

00:48:00.127 --> 00:48:02.421
Then why pick Ryu Eun-jung
as your desk buddy?

00:48:02.504 --> 00:48:04.506
Because I wanted her as a desk buddy.

00:48:05.007 --> 00:48:08.677
Why would you pick her as your buddy
when you like another girl?

00:48:09.595 --> 00:48:12.014
-Eun-jung really likes you.
-I never said that.

00:48:12.723 --> 00:48:14.808
But you wrote Sang-yeon a love letter!

00:48:15.309 --> 00:48:18.020
You acting like that is confusing girls.

00:48:18.520 --> 00:48:20.105
That means you're two-timing!

00:48:21.523 --> 00:48:24.234
-Two-timing?
-Why are you yelling in our classroom?

00:48:24.318 --> 00:48:25.527
You stay out of it!

00:48:25.611 --> 00:48:29.072
Why should I? He says he wanted
to sit with her. What's the big deal?

00:48:29.615 --> 00:48:30.908
Incredible.

00:48:30.991 --> 00:48:34.703
-Why did you want to sit with Eun-jung?
-Because she's easy to be around.

00:48:34.786 --> 00:48:37.706
She was already my desk buddy,
so I was comfortable with her.

00:48:37.789 --> 00:48:40.208
That means you didn't pick her
because you liked her!

00:48:40.292 --> 00:48:43.712
So you picked her
because she was an easy choice?

00:48:43.795 --> 00:48:47.299
So what if she was an easy choice?
Why are you overreacting?

00:48:47.382 --> 00:48:49.676
What did you say? Overreacting?

00:48:50.177 --> 00:48:53.347
How dare you!
You think Eun-jung's a pushover?

00:49:04.066 --> 00:49:05.817
-Hello, ma'am.
-Hi, girls.

00:49:06.443 --> 00:49:08.111
-Hello.
-Hi.

00:49:08.195 --> 00:49:09.571
Wait, Eun-jung?

00:49:54.533 --> 00:49:57.202
Under the TV. Second drawer…

00:50:17.764 --> 00:50:20.434
It felt strange.

00:50:23.061 --> 00:50:24.563
It was all quite strange.

00:50:26.481 --> 00:50:30.068
It's not like I hadn't known that
Sang-yeon was Ms. Yoon's daughter,

00:50:31.445 --> 00:50:32.946
but I felt deflated,

00:50:33.822 --> 00:50:35.365
as though I'd just found out.

00:50:39.995 --> 00:50:40.954
Complete.

00:50:42.748 --> 00:50:45.042
Being there, Sang-yeon appeared

00:50:45.834 --> 00:50:47.294
complete.

00:50:48.670 --> 00:50:50.255
Entirely out of reach,

00:50:50.756 --> 00:50:53.341
like somebody I could never beat.

00:50:57.012 --> 00:50:58.597
It was that house.

00:51:00.307 --> 00:51:01.141
There.

00:51:02.517 --> 00:51:04.478
Cheon Sang-yeon was the one
who lived there.

00:51:40.764 --> 00:51:46.937
YOU'RE SO LUCKY

00:51:47.020 --> 00:51:48.063
Who are you?

00:51:53.568 --> 00:51:55.779
Who… are you?

00:51:59.658 --> 00:52:03.161
I'm, well… Ryu Eun-jung.

00:52:04.287 --> 00:52:06.248
This short middle school kid would,

00:52:06.790 --> 00:52:07.958
three years later,

00:52:09.042 --> 00:52:10.710
become my first love.

00:52:13.964 --> 00:52:15.132
Let's do this, Ms. Ryu.

00:52:18.343 --> 00:52:20.971
How can you say that
after reading a mere draft?

00:52:21.054 --> 00:52:22.681
Yes, it's a draft,

00:52:23.807 --> 00:52:25.308
but I think it'll be good.

00:52:26.017 --> 00:52:26.893
You do?

00:52:29.229 --> 00:52:32.399
It does feel nice to hear that from you.

00:52:32.899 --> 00:52:35.944
Why did you stop writing here?

00:52:36.444 --> 00:52:38.905
Things were getting juicy.
It should write itself.

00:52:43.910 --> 00:52:46.121
I guess something stopped me.

00:52:48.707 --> 00:52:50.750
I must have forgotten

00:52:51.918 --> 00:52:56.506
that writing about those times
would mean talking about Sang-hak oppa.

00:52:58.091 --> 00:53:00.302
Why? You can't talk about him?

00:53:02.345 --> 00:53:03.805
It's not that I can't.

00:53:04.389 --> 00:53:08.560
This person named Sang-hak.
He's Ms. Cheon's brother, right?

00:53:13.315 --> 00:53:15.817
Is it uncomfortable for you
to write about him?

00:53:16.818 --> 00:53:19.988
Why? How intense
was this first love of yours?

00:53:21.823 --> 00:53:24.868
If it was three years later,
you'd only have been in eighth grade.

00:53:26.536 --> 00:53:27.954
I guess so.

00:53:28.997 --> 00:53:30.540
Either way,

00:53:31.291 --> 00:53:34.294
he had a huge influence on me.

00:53:36.004 --> 00:53:37.505
Just write it.

00:53:50.060 --> 00:53:52.020
I don't know this number. Who could it be?

00:53:52.729 --> 00:53:53.939
Don't mind me.

00:53:56.816 --> 00:53:57.901
Hello?

00:54:00.820 --> 00:54:02.614
Yes, this is she. Who's calling?

00:54:07.869 --> 00:54:08.870
Sang-yeon?

00:54:12.082 --> 00:54:12.958
Cheon?

00:54:19.506 --> 00:54:21.383
Right. One second.

00:54:28.682 --> 00:54:30.809
Was it really Ms. Cheon?

00:54:35.939 --> 00:54:36.898
I guess so.

00:54:37.732 --> 00:54:38.775
What did she say?

00:54:40.777 --> 00:54:43.363
She wants to meet.
She needs to tell me something.

00:54:43.989 --> 00:54:44.864
Tell you what?

00:54:47.450 --> 00:54:50.161
Maybe she wants to offer you a project.

00:54:50.662 --> 00:54:53.873
Everyone from film production
is moving over to series these days.

00:55:19.482 --> 00:55:20.567
It's been a while.

00:55:22.068 --> 00:55:23.111
Why did you call?

00:55:32.996 --> 00:55:34.247
It's just

00:55:34.831 --> 00:55:36.708
you seemed so frigid.

00:55:39.961 --> 00:55:42.756
I remember when I'd use my mom
as an excuse.

00:55:44.841 --> 00:55:47.927
Back in the day,
whenever you were mad at me,

00:55:48.011 --> 00:55:49.512
I'd bring up my mom,

00:55:50.013 --> 00:55:52.599
and it would soften you up
and make you agree to anything.

00:55:58.772 --> 00:55:59.898
I've been practicing

00:56:01.483 --> 00:56:03.276
what I wanted to say to you today,

00:56:04.861 --> 00:56:07.238
but now that I'm here,
I can't get the words out.

00:56:07.322 --> 00:56:08.948
Just say it.

00:56:09.657 --> 00:56:11.618
Apparently, I'm dying.

00:56:18.917 --> 00:56:19.751
What?

00:56:24.589 --> 00:56:27.967
I'm only 43 years old.

00:56:37.977 --> 00:56:38.895
Are you

00:56:40.313 --> 00:56:41.147
ill?

00:56:41.731 --> 00:56:42.565
Cancer.

00:56:43.942 --> 00:56:44.901
It's terminal.

00:56:51.783 --> 00:56:54.494
It's unbelievable, isn't it?
I feel the same way.

00:56:59.874 --> 00:57:01.167
Hang on a minute.

00:57:06.548 --> 00:57:09.175
I have a favor to ask you.

00:57:15.473 --> 00:57:16.349
What is this?

00:57:27.694 --> 00:57:28.945
Keep looking.

00:57:40.415 --> 00:57:41.291
That's right.

00:57:42.292 --> 00:57:44.085
They've made films about it,

00:57:45.003 --> 00:57:46.296
so you might know

00:57:47.714 --> 00:57:50.550
about assisted dying.

00:57:58.057 --> 00:57:59.893
I know it's not an easy ask…

00:58:02.395 --> 00:58:04.772
but I really hope you'll help me.

00:58:11.613 --> 00:58:12.614
Won't you

00:58:13.823 --> 00:58:15.700
come with me?

01:01:52.083 --> 01:01:57.088
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi